<recipe>
    <name>Cheesecake Ice Cream</name>
    <indexCharacter>c</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add remaining ingredients and blend well.

Freeze mixture in ice cream freezer according to unit's instructions. Once the mixture has reached a soft serve consistency, spoon the mixture back into a lidded container and harden in the freezer at least 1 hour before serving.

Yield: 1 quart</instructions>
